Package info6205.Graph.Problems.TravellingSalesMan.Algorithm.ThreeOpt

Class ThreeOpt<NodeValue,NodeKeyValue,EdgeWeight extends Comparable<EdgeWeight>>

java.lang.Object
info6205.Graph.Problems.TravellingSalesMan.Algorithm.ThreeOpt.ThreeOpt<NodeValue,NodeKeyValue,EdgeWeight>
Type Parameters:
NodeValue - the node value type
NodeKeyValue - the node key value type
EdgeWeight - the edge weight type which extends Comparable
public class ThreeOpt<NodeValue,NodeKeyValue,EdgeWeight extends Comparable<EdgeWeight>> extends Object
The ThreeOpt class is used to implement the 3-opt algorithm.. This algorithm takes a set of nodes as input and iteratively optimizes the tour using three different kinds of exchanges between three edges in the tour until no further improvement can be made.

      Parameters:
      parallelism - number of parallel threads
      tour - TSP Tour, list of nodes
      graphWeight - current weight of the TSP tour
      temp - The initial temperature for the simulated annealing algorithm.
      coolingRate - The cooling rate for the simulated annealing algorithm.
      maxIteration - The maximum number of iterations for the simulated annealing algorithm.
      equilibriumCountForTemp - The number of iterations to wait for equilibrium before reducing the temperature.
      equilibriumIncrease - The increase factor for the equilibrium count.
      returnMinimum - Whether to return only the minimum tour found by the algorithm and replace current tour with minimum tour
      benchMarking - Whether to enable benchmarking mode for the algorithm.

    • runSimulatedAnnealing

      public Double runSimulatedAnnealing(List<Node<NodeValue,NodeKeyValue>> order, Double graphWeight, double temp, double coolingRate, long maxIteration, int equilibriumCountForTemp, int equilibriumIncrease)
      Runs the simulated annealing algorithm to find the minimum weight Hamiltonian path in the given graph.
      Parameters:
      order - a list of nodes representing the graph
      graphWeight - the weight of the initial TSP path
      temp - the starting temperature
      coolingRate - the cooling rate by which the temp is decreased
      maxIteration - the maximum number of iterations to run
      equilibriumCountForTemp - the number of times to iterate at each temperature before cooling
      equilibriumIncrease - the amount to increase the equilibrium count for each temperature
      Returns:
      the minimum weight Hamiltonian path found by the algorithm
      Throws:
      Exception - if an error occurs while running the algorithm
